<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - REAR COVER, FLYWHEEL, and POWER STEERING GEAR DRIVE - Installation
        - Flywheel
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26513.3.6" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Flywheel</title>
        <figure id="f2651339" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/D0704.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Flywheel on guide pins</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two flywheel guide pins (made locally) in crankshaft flange at approximately 3
                o'clock and 9 o'clock.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align dowel hole in flywheel with crankshaft secondary flange dowel and slide flywheel onto
                guide pins.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align reinforcement ring with dowel and slide over guide pins. Make sure lip on outer
                circumference of ring faces the transmission.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, use new bolts to install flywheel.</para>
            </caution>
            <caution>
                <para>Do not use anti-seize compounds, grease or lubricants. Each has an adverse effect on torque
                    results.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>New phosphate coated bolts do not require oil before torquing.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two new M10 x 77 bolts to secure flywheel to crankshaft. Remove both guide pins.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install eight remaining M10 x 77 bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651340" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/D0739.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="312px"
                     box="no"/>
            <caption>Torque sequence for flywheel</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Snug bolts in the sequence to 1 to 7 N&#183;m (12 to 60 lbf&#183;in).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Torque all bolts in the sequence to the special torque .</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reinstall safety guards, shields, and covers.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure tools, cleanliness covers, loose parts, and service equipment are removed from the
                engine area.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
